1. Running the server
	python manage.py runserver 8080

	That configures the port to 8080 (it's 8000 by default)

2. Follow steps on tutorial (below) to make the database (the environment) and then start building up the model

https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/intro/tutorial01/

3. Define the model for the application (we don't care about the backend - it will just feed data back to the user in plaintext for verification, the second step is the most important.
